title: Check for Apple XSAN,
agents: darwin
author: Jeremy Leggat <jleggat@asu.edu>
license: GPL
distribution:
description:
 This check makes use of the output of a working {cvadmin} on
 an OS X system. If the XSAN is properly configured and {cvadmin}
 is installed, then the agent will output output a list of LUNs visible
 to the node and the corresponding HBA port used to communicate with that LUN.

item:
 Disk Volume Name for the paths.

inventory:
 One item is created for each Xsan disk volumes visible to the local system.

perfdata:

[parameters]
